    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@rayrutjes We are open to discussion for an API that does not requires adding more classnames. The issue is that the more state we inline into the classes API, the less easy it is to document it.\n\nAlso utlimately this is a design decision but if you hide the pagination when there's only one page, you do provide less context for the user. If there's no pagination on a webpage (or if the pagination is hidden/shown given some context I do not decide), then the user might think \"Well, maybe there's more result, maybe that the only page, but I can't tell it because I don't know how this page is built\".\n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-11T09:57:35Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1402#issuecomment-252865663",
