  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Found another solution - I'm using Vue, but should be doable across the board.\r\n\r\n1. Use ais-stats to get number of pages\r\n```vue\r\n<ais-stats>\r\n  <template slot-scope=\"{ nbHits, page, nbPages }\">\r\n    <span\r\n      class=\"-s-results-found\"\r\n      v-html=\"getResultText(nbHits, page, nbPages)\"></span>\r\n  </template>\r\n</ais-stats>\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. As you run the function to generate the result text, you can decide to show the pagination\r\n```js\r\ngetResultText(nbHits, page, nbPages) {\r\n  // Decide to show pagination\r\n  if (nbPages > 1) eventBus.isShowingPagination = true\r\n\r\n  // Return text\r\n  let text = ''\r\n  if (nbHits === 0)\r\n    text = `<span class=\"-s-hidden-good\">W: </span>No products found`\r\n  if (nbHits === 1)\r\n    text = `<span class=\"-s-hidden-good\">W: </span>${ nbHits } product found`\r\n  if (nbHits > 1)\r\n    text = `<span class=\"-s-hidden-good\">W: </span>${ nbHits } products found`\r\n  if (nbPages > 1) text += ` - Page ${ page + 1 } of ${ nbPages }`\r\n\r\n  return text\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Now you can show/hide your pagination conditionally\r\n```vue\r\n<ais-pagination\r\n      :show-next=\"false\"\r\n      :show-previous=\"false\"\r\n      :class-names=\"{ 'ais-Pagination': '-s-srp__pagination' }\"\r\n      :class=\"{ '-s-hidden-good': !isShowingPagination }\"\r\n      @page-change=\"onPageChange\"/>\r\n```\r\n\r\nBest of luck",
    "created_at": "2020-01-10T07:56:20Z",
